tldr: The user requested a comprehensive aesthetic review and improvement for
  their sleep questionnaire app. The agent implemented a new sleep-themed color
  palette, redesigned key UI components and sections, and fixed a console error
  related to null input values, resulting in a polished and cohesive user
  experience.
overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The agent began by
  thoroughly reviewing the existing visual design, identifying areas like the
  color palette, layout, and form elements that needed refinement. The approach
  involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color palette using deep
  indigos, purples, and teal accents. Key components like the main form layout,
  progress bar, intro section, and individual form fields (checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders) were redesigned with improved visual hierarchy, hover
  states, and subtle thematic elements. All questionnaire sections were updated
  for consistent styling, replacing old gray boxes with refined card-like
  groupings. Additionally, a console error related to  values being passed
  to input fields was identified and fixed by modifying the base
  component. A final round of aesthetic adjustments ensured all alerts used the
  new theme colors, section borders were more defined, and report section card
  headers were consistent. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional, and
  calming application experience.
